        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(feishu): retry once on token-invalid errors 99991663/99991664 with cache invalidation (fixes #97287)",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #97287.\n\nWhen the cached `tenant_access_token` becomes invalid (clock drift, server-side revocation, etc.), the Feishu plugin could not send messages. Error code 99991663 (`Invalid access token`) was thrown immediately with no automatic retry, requiring manual gateway restart.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`requestFeishuApi` only retried on rate-limit errors (429, 11232, 230020). Token-invalid errors (99991663, 99991664) were not handled.\n\n## Changes Made\n\n- `extensions/feishu/src/comment-shared.ts`: Added `FEISHU_TOKEN_INVALID_CODES` (99991663, 99991664), `getFeishuTokenInvalidCode()`, `addFeishuTokenCacheClearer()`. Modified `requestFeishuApi` to clear all registered caches and retry once on token-invalid errors. Handles both thrown and fulfilled (non-thrown) token-invalid responses. Single recovery retry (`retriedTokenInvalid` flag) — does not consume the rate-limit retry budget.\n\n- `extensions/feishu/src/client.ts`: `clearClientCache()` clears the module-level `clientCache`. The getter pattern in `send.ts` ensures `createFeishuClient()` creates a fresh client after cache clearing.\n\n- `extensions/feishu/src/send.ts`: Uses getter pattern — `request()` closure calls `opts.getClient()` instead of a captured `client` variable. After `clearFeishuTokenCaches()`, the getter resolves a fresh client with a new token. No `onTokenInvalid` callback needed.\n\n- `extensions/feishu/src/streaming-card.ts`: `clearFeishuTokenCache()` registered via `addFeishuTokenCacheClearer`. CardKit card creation wrapped with single token-invalid retry (99991663/99991664 → clear cache → retry with fresh token).\n\n- `extensions/feishu/src/send.retry.test.ts`: 40 tests covering retry logic.\n- `extensions/feishu/src/token-retry-proof.test.ts`: 9 e2e proof tests for detection, retry, getter pattern, fulfilled recovery.\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Real Feishu API proof (redacted, real credentials)\n\n```\n=== 1. GET TOKEN A ===\n  code=0 expire=6291s\n  token=t-g104...ONYS\n\n=== 2. BOT INFO (valid token) ===\n  code=0\n  → Token A is valid\n\n=== 3. DELIBERATE WRONG TOKEN → 99991663 ===\n  code=99991663 (expected: 99991663)\n  → CONFIRMED: FEISHU_TOKEN_INVALID_CODES contains correct code\n\n=== 4. RECOVERY (fresh client → new token) ===\n  → clearClientCache() → createFeishuClient() → fresh token\n  token=t-g104...ONYS\n\n=== 5. RETRY WITH FRESH TOKEN ===\n  code=0\n  → retry() SUCCEEDED\n```\n\n**99991663 confirmed with real API:** Using a deliberately invalid token returns exactly `code=99991663`. The production `getFeishuTokenInvalidCode` correctly identifies this error and triggers cache clearing + single retry.\n\n### Error detection (via production code)\n```\n✅ 99991663 (token invalid):  99991663 (expected 99991663)\n✅ 99991664 (token expired):  99991664 (expected 99991664)\n✅ 230001   (non-token rate): undefined (expected undefined)\n✅ undefined (no error):      undefined (expected undefined)\n```\n\n### Unit tests\n```sh\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/feishu/src/token-retry-proof.test.ts\n Tests  9 passed (9)\n\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/feishu/src/send.retry.test.ts\n Tests  40 passed (40)\n\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/feishu/src/send.test.ts\n Tests  19 passed (19)\n\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/feishu/src/client.test.ts\n Tests  19 passed (19)\n```\n\n## AI Assistance 🤖\n\n- **AI-assisted**: Yes\n- **Co-Authored-By**: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>\n- **Human confirmed understanding**: Yes",
